Quickstrike:









Quickstrike pondered after Transulas. His laugh was a little un-nerving. 
What he said about Black Archnia didn't sound too realistic to him right 
now. And how did he know he had an affection over her? Love wasn't on his 
mind, it was how the was going to get used to this and who he was going to 
settle down with as ally.

He turned his head back to the stick on his foreclaw. He guestured to 
Transulas for his favor with the two foot long leaf that he was going to use 
to tie down the brace. He hoped that he would tie it down too. He knew he 
was going to have a fit with it.

"Where are we's goin'?" he added.
